HEADWORD: Two-throw
<hw>Two"-throw`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Capable of being thrown or cranked in two directions,
usually opposite to one another; <as>as, a <ex>two-throw</ex> crank; a
<ex>two-throw</ex> switch</as>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Having two crank
set near together and opposite to one another; <as>as, a
<ex>two-throw</ex> crank shaft</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

